---
import { Picture } from "astro:assets"

import PersonImageLabel  from "./PersonImageLabel.astro"
import EngineerImg from "./images/engineer-nathan-1.png"
---

<section class="bg-white">
  <div class="m-auto flex max-w-screen-xl flex-col items-center gap-12 p-8 text-black md:flex-row md:items-start md:gap-24 lg:pt-16">
    <div class="flex flex-col items-center">
      <div class="relative max-h-80 min-h-80 min-w-80 max-w-80 rounded-2xl bg-gold-25">
        <div class="grid-background" style={{"--grid-background-spacing": "30px"}}/>
        <Picture
            class="absolute bottom-0 left-[6%] !w-[90%]"
            sizes="(max-width: 64rem) 31rem, 41rem"
            formats={["webp", "avif"]}
            breakpoints={[496, 656]}
            src={EngineerImg}
            alt="Panfactum Engineer"
        />
      </div>
      <PersonImageLabel title="Nathan H." subtitle="Sr. Dev Ops Engineer"/>
    </div>
    <div class="flex flex-col gap-2">
      <div class="font-bold text-brand-700">
        The Panfactum Approach
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-pretty font-machina text-4xl font-semibold">
        Master Your Cloud Platform
      </h2>
      <p class="text-lg text-gray-dark-mode-700">
        It's no secret that teams that master their cloud platforms unlock new capabilities and ship software faster, cheaper, and more reliably than their competition.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-1 text-lg text-gray-dark-mode-700">
         As a result, we launched <span class="font-medium">Panfactum</span>Plus with one goal:  
      </p>
      <p class="mt-1 text-lg font-bold text-gray-dark-mode-700">Get a 10x cloud engineer starting at $999 / mo.</p>
      <p class="mt-1 text-lg text-gray-dark-mode-700">
        How do we do that? Our engineers leverage our{" "}<a href="/" class="cursor-pointer underline decoration-dotted decoration-2 underline-offset-4">open-source cloud framework</a>{" "}to move 10x faster than other engineers and then pass the savings on to you.
     </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>